# === OpenFOAM build artifacts ===
# wmake compiles into a platform-specific subfolder under each solver's Make/
# (e.g. Make/linux64GccDPInt32Opt/) and writes the executable to $FOAM_USER_APPBIN,
# which normally lives outside the repo anyway. Never commit these.
Make/*/
lnInclude/
*.o
*.dep
*.a
*.so

# === OpenFOAM run-time outputs (regenerated by blockMesh / solvers / Allrun) ===
# Numbered time directories written during a run. Keep 0/ and 0.orig/ (initial
# conditions) but ignore every other numeric time step folder.
[1-9]*/
[0-9]*.[0-9]*/
processor[0-9]*/
postProcessing/
VTK/
log.*
*.log

# NOTE: constant/polyMesh/ is intentionally NOT ignored here. DNSCase01 ships
# a pre-baked mesh that must stay tracked; DNSCase02 doesn't have one yet and
# generates it locally via blockMesh. If you regenerate DNSCase02's mesh and
# don't want to commit it, ignore it case-by-case (e.g. a case-local
# .gitignore inside case/DNSCase02/) rather than a blanket rule here, so
# DNSCase01's tracked mesh isn't accidentally caught too.

# === Python (post-processing scripts) ===
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# === OS / editor clutter ===
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vscode/
.idea/
